### SGS Projects API - Timesheet Management

### 1. Ottieni tutti i timesheet (ODBC SAP HANA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Ottieni un timesheet specifico (ODBC SAP HANA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/123
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Ottieni timesheet per dipendente (ODBC SAP HANA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/employee/EMP001
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Ottieni timesheet per progetto (ODBC SAP HANA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/project/PRJ001
Accept: application/json

###

### 5. Ottieni timesheet per intervallo di date (ODBC SAP HANA)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/daterange?startDate=2024-01-01&endDate=2024-01-31
Accept: application/json

###

### 6. Crea un nuovo timesheet (SAP B1 Service Layer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "date": "2024-01-15T00:00:00",
  "employeeId": "EMP001",
  "projectId": "PRJ001",
  "activityId": "ACT001",
  "hours": 8.5,
  "description": "Sviluppo funzionalità API"
}

###

### 7. Aggiorna un timesheet esistente (SAP B1 Service Layer)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "docEntry": 123,
  "date": "2024-01-15T00:00:00",
  "employeeId": "EMP001",
  "projectId": "PRJ001",
  "activityId": "ACT001",
  "hours": 9.0,
  "description": "Sviluppo funzionalità API - Aggiornato"
}

###

### 8. Elimina un timesheet (SAP B1 Service Layer)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/timesheet/123

###

### Variabili di ambiente
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
